# mehfil.DEV — Project Overview

## Brand

**mehfil.DEV** is an AI code rescue & production engineering agency. It converts broken AI-generated prototypes (Bolt.new, Cursor, Lovable, Replit) into production-grade Next.js / Web3 applications. All purchase CTAs point to Fiverr (`https://www.fiverr.com/foxlancerr`).

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|-------|--------|
| Framework | Next.js 16 App Router (see AGENTS.md — breaking changes vs prior versions) |
| UI | React 19 + TypeScript |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 via `@tailwindcss/postcss` |
| Animation | Framer Motion 11 (scroll-triggered `useInView`) |
| State | Zustand 5 |
| Icons | Lucide React |
| Accordion | Radix UI `@radix-ui/react-accordion` |
| Utility | `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` via `lib/utils.ts` → `cn()` |

## Architecture

Single-page marketing site (`app/page.tsx`) composing 12 section components in `components/`. No API routes, no auth, no database. One route only: `/`.

Section order: `AnimatedGrid` → `CursorGlow` → `Navbar` → `Hero` → `ValueAnchor` → `ServicePillars` → `CaseStudies` → `Deployments` → `Testimonials` → `FAQ` → `Pricing` → `Footer`.

## Non-Negotiables

- Every component is a **Client Component** (`"use client"`) — keep it that way unless explicitly changing to Server Components
- All class merging uses `cn()` from `lib/utils.ts` — never raw string concatenation
- Dark theme only: `<html className="dark">` — no light mode toggle
- Tailwind v4 syntax: use `@import "tailwindcss"` in CSS, NOT `@tailwind` directives
- No autoprefixer in postcss — Tailwind v4 handles it natively
- Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before using any Next.js API
